g702.definition: [Ἀρέτας] of foreign origin; Aretas, an Arabian

g703.definition: [ἀρέτη] from the same as {{g730}}; properly, manliness (valor), i.e. excellence (intrinsic or attributed)

g704.definition: [ἀρήν] perhaps the same as {{g730}}; a lamb (as a male)

g707.definition: [Ἀριμαθαία] of Hebrew origin ({{h7414}}); Arimathæa (or Ramah), a place in Palestine

g708.definition: [Ἀρίσταρχος] from the same as {{g712}} and {{g757}}; best ruling; Aristarchus, a Macedonian

g709.definition: [ἀριστάω] from {{g712}}; to take the principle meal

g710.definition: [ἀριστερός] apparently a comparative of the same as {{g712}}; the left hand (as second-best)

g711.definition: [Ἀριστόβουλος] from the same as {{g712}} and {{g1012}}; best counselling; Aristoboulus, a Christian

g712.definition: [ἄριστον] apparently neuter of a superlative from the same as {{g730}}; the best meal (or breakfast; perhaps from ἦρι ("early")), i.e. luncheon

g714.definition: [ἀρκέω] apparently a primary verb (but probably akin to {{g142}} through the idea of raising a barrier); properly, to ward off, i.e. (by implication) to avail (figuratively, be satisfactory)

g715.definition: [ἄρκτος] probably from {{g714}}; a bear (as obstructing by ferocity)

g716.definition: [ἅρμα] probably from {{g142}} (perhaps with {{g1}} (as a particle of union) prefixed); a chariot (as raised or fitted together (compare {{g719}}))

g717.definition: [Ἀρμαγεδδών] of Hebrew origin ({{h2022}} and {{h4023}}); Armageddon (or Har-Meggiddon), a symbolic name

g718.definition: [ἁρμόζω] from {{g719}}; to joint, i.e. (figuratively) to woo (reflexively, to betroth)

g719.definition: [ἁρμός] from the same as {{g716}}; an articulation (of the body)

g720.definition: [ἀρνέομαι] perhaps from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the middle voice of {{g4483}}; to contradict, i.e. disavow, reject, abnegate

g726.definition: [ἁρπάζω] from a derivative of {{g138}}; to seize (in various applications)

g728.definition: [ἀῤῥαβών] of Hebrew origin ({{h6162}}); a pledge, i.e. part of the purchase-money or property given in advance as security for the rest

g729.definition: [ἄῤῥαφος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of the same as {{g4476}}; unsewed, i.e. of a single piece

g730.definition: [ἄῤῥην]   or ἄρσηνprobably from {{g142}}; male (as stronger for lifting)

g731.definition: [ἄῤῥητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the same as {{g4490}}; unsaid, i.e. (by implication) inexpressible

g732.definition: [ἄῤῥωστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g4517}}; infirm

g734.definition: [Ἀρτεμάς] contracted from a compound of {{g735}} and {{g1435}}; gift of Artemis; Artemas (or Artemidorus), a Christian

g735.definition: [Ἄρτεμις] probably from the same as {{g736}}; prompt; Artemis, the name of a Grecian goddess borrowed by the Asiatics for one of their deities

g736.definition: [ἀρτέμων] from a derivative of {{g737}}; properly, something ready (or else more remotely from {{g142}} (compare {{g740}}); something hung up), i.e. (specially) the topsail (rather foresail or jib) of a vessel

g737.definition: [ἄρτι] adverb from a derivative of {{g142}} (compare {{g740}}) through the idea of suspension; just now

g738.definition: [ἀρτιγέννητος] from {{g737}} and {{g1084}}; just born, i.e. (figuratively) a young convert

g740.definition: [ἄρτος] from {{g142}}; bread (as raised) or a loaf

g741.definition: [ἀρτύω] from a presumed derivative of {{g142}}; to prepare, i.e. spice (with stimulating condiments)

g742.definition: [Ἀρφαξάδ] of Hebrew origin ({{h775}}); Arphaxad, a post-diluvian patriarch

g745.definition: [Ἀρχέλαος] from {{g757}} and {{g2994}}; people-ruling; Archelaus, a Jewish king

g746.definition: [ἀρχή] from {{g756}}; (properly abstract) a commencement, or (concretely) chief (in various applications of order, time, place, or rank)

g748.definition: [ἀρχιερατικός] from {{g746}} and a derivative of {{g2413}}; high-priestly

g749.definition: [ἀρχιερεύς] from {{g746}} and {{g2409}}; the high-priest (literally, of the Jews, typically, Christ); by extension a chief priest

g751.definition: [Ἄρχιππος] from {{g746}} and {{g2462}}; horse-ruler; Archippus, a Christian

g752.definition: [ἀρχισυνάγωγος] from {{g746}} and {{g4864}}; director of the synagogue services

g753.definition: [ἀρχιτέκτων] from {{g746}} and {{g5045}}; a chief constructor, i.e. "architect"

g755.definition: [ἀρχιτρίκλινος] from {{g746}} and a compound of {{g5140}} and {{g2827}} (a dinner-bed, because composed of three couches); director of the entertainment

g756.definition: [ἄρχομαι] middle voice of {{g757}} (through the implication, of precedence); to commence (in order of time)

g757.definition: [ἄρχω] a primary verb; to be first (in political rank or power)

g758.definition: [ἄρχων] present participle of {{g757}}; a first (in rank or power)

g759.definition: [ἄρωμα] from {{g142}} (in the sense of sending off scent); an aromatic

g760.definition: [Ἀσά] of Hebrew origin ({{h609}}); Asa, an Israelite

g761.definition: [ἀσάλευτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4531}}; unshaken, i.e. (by implication) immovable (figuratively)

g762.definition: [ἄσβεστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4570}}; not extinguished, i.e. (by implication) perpetual

g764.definition: [ἀσεβέω] from {{g765}}; to be (by implied act) impious or wicked

g765.definition: [ἀσεβής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g4576}}; irreverent, i.e. (by extension) impious or wicked

g766.definition: [ἀσέλγεια] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed σελγής (of uncertain derivation, but apparently meaning continent); licentiousness (sometimes including other vices)

g767.definition: [ἄσημος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g4591}}; unmarked, i.e. (figuratively) ignoble

g768.definition: [Ἀσήρ] of Hebrew origin ({{h836}}); Aser (i.e. Asher), an Israelite tribe

g769.definition: [ἀσθένεια] from {{g772}}; feebleness (of mind or body); by implication, malady; morally, frailty

g770.definition: [ἀσθενέω] from {{g772}}; to be feeble (in any sense)

g772.definition: [ἀσθενής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g4599}}; strengthless (in various applications, literal, figurative and moral)

g773.definition: [Ἀσία] of uncertain derivation; Asia, i.e. Asia Minor, or (usually) only its western shore

g774.definition: [Ἀσιανός] from {{g773}}; an Asian (i.e. Asiatic) or an inhabitant of Asia

g775.definition: [Ἀσιάρχης] from {{g773}} and {{g746}}; an Asiarch or president of the public festivities in a city of Asia Minor

g777.definition: [ἄσιτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4621}}; without (taking) food

g778.definition: [ἀσκέω] probably from the same as {{g4632}}; to elaborate, i.e. (figuratively) train (by implication, strive)

g779.definition: [ἀσκός] from the same as {{g778}}; a leathern (or skin) bag used as a bottle

g780.definition: [ἀσμένως] adverb from a derivative of the base of {{g2237}}; with pleasure

g781.definition: [ἄσοφος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4680}}; unwise

g782.definition: [ἀσπάζομαι] from {{g1}} (as a particle of union) and a presumed form of {{g4685}}; to enfold in the arms, i.e. (by implication) to salute, (figuratively) to welcome

g783.definition: [ἀσπασμός] from {{g782}}; a greeting (in person or by letter)

g784.definition: [ἄσπιλος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4695}}; unblemished (physically or morally)

g785.definition: [ἀσπίς] of uncertain derivation; a buckler (or round shield); used of a serpent (as coiling itself), probably the "asp"

g786.definition: [ἄσπονδος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4689}}; literally, without libation (which usually accompanied a treaty), i.e. (by implication) truceless

g787.definition: [ἀσσάριον] of Latin origin; an assarius or as, a Roman coin

g788.definition: [ἆσσον] neuter comparative of the base of {{g1451}}; more nearly, i.e. very near

g789.definition: [Ἄσσος] probably of foreign origin; Assus, a city of Asia MInor

g790.definition: [ἀστατέω] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2476}}; to be non-stationary, i.e. (figuratively) homeless

g791.definition: [ἀστεῖος] from ἄστυ (a city); urbane, i.e. (by implication) handsome

g792.definition: [ἀστήρ] probably from the base of {{g4766}}; a star (as strown over the sky), literally or figuratively

g793.definition: [ἀστήρικτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g4741}}; unfixed, i.e. (figuratively) vacillating

g794.definition: [ἄστοργος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of στέργω (to cherish affectionately); hard-hearted towards kindred

g795.definition: [ἀστοχέω] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and στοίχος (an aim); to miss the mark, i.e. (figuratively) deviate from truth

g797.definition: [ἀστράπτω] probably from  {{g792}}; to flash as lightning

g798.definition: [ἄστρον] neuter from {{g792}}; properly, a constellation; put for a single star (natural or artificial)

g799.definition: [Ἀσύγκριτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4793}}; incomparable; Asyncritus, a Christian

g800.definition: [ἀσύμφωνος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4859}}; inharmonious (figuratively)
